battery_saver.doc: OBSOLETE replaced by mobile_fps_* - Battery saver mode. 0=off, 1=on

benchframe.doc: Takes a snapshot of a particular frame in a time demo.

binddefaults.doc: Bind all keys to their default values.

bindss.doc: Bind a key for a particular splitscreen player.

bot_add_t.doc: bot_add_t <type> <difficulty> <name> - Adds a terrorist bot matching the given criteria.

bot_all_weapons.doc: Allows the bots to use all weapons

bot_allow_grenades.doc: If nonzero, bots may use grenades.

bot_allow_machine_guns.doc: If nonzero, bots may use the machine gun.

bot_allow_pistols.doc: If nonzero, bots may use pistols.

bot_allow_rifles.doc: If nonzero, bots may use rifles.

bot_allow_rogues.doc: If nonzero, bots may occasionally go 'rogue'. Rogue bots do not obey radio commands, nor pursue scenario goals.

bot_allow_shotguns.doc: If nonzero, bots may use shotguns.

bot_allow_snipers.doc: If nonzero, bots may use sniper rifles.

bot_allow_sub_machine_guns.doc: If nonzero, bots may use sub-machine guns.

bot_autodifficulty_threshold_high.doc: Upper bound above Average Human Contribution Score that a bot must be above to change its difficulty

bot_autodifficulty_threshold_low.doc: Lower bound below Average Human Contribution Score that a bot must be below to change its difficulty

bot_chatter.doc: Control how bots talk. Allowed values: 'off', 'radio', 'minimal', or 'normal'.

bot_controllable.doc: Determines whether bots can be controlled by players

bot_coop_idle_max_vision_distance.doc: Max distance bots can see targets (in coop) when they are idle, dormant, hiding or asleep.

bot_defer_to_human_goals.doc: If nonzero and there is a human on the team, the bots will not do the scenario tasks.

bot_defer_to_human_items.doc: If nonzero and there is a human on the team, the bots will not get scenario items.

bot_difficulty.doc: Defines the skill of bots joining the game.  Values are: 0=easy, 1=normal, 2=hard, 3=expert.

bot_dont_shoot.doc: If nonzero, bots will not fire weapons (for debugging).

bot_goto_mark.doc: Sends a bot to the marked nav area (useful for testing navigation meshes)

bot_goto_selected.doc: Sends a bot to the selected nav area (useful for testing navigation meshes)

bot_ignore_enemies.doc: If nonzero, bots will ignore enemies (for debugging).

bot_ignore_players.doc: Bots will not see non-bot players.

bot_join_after_player.doc: If nonzero, bots wait until a player joins before entering the game.

bot_join_team.doc: Determines the team bots will join into. Allowed values: 'any', 'T', or 'CT'.

bot_kick.doc: bot_kick <all> <t|ct> <type> <difficulty> <name> - Kicks a specific bot, or all bots, matching the given criteria.

bot_kill.doc: bot_kill <all> <t|ct> <type> <difficulty> <name> - Kills a specific bot, or all bots, matching the given criteria.

bot_knives_only.doc: Restricts the bots to only using knives

bot_loadout.doc: bots are given these items at round start

bot_max_visible_smoke_length.doc: Bots will see players through smoke clouds up to this length.

bot_max_vision_distance_override.doc: Max distance bots can see targets.

bot_mimic.doc: Bot uses usercmd of player by index.

bot_mimic_spec_buttons.doc: +attack, +jump etc are used for spectator control instead of being passed on to spectated bot

bot_pistols_only.doc: Restricts the bots to only using pistols

bot_place.doc: bot_place - Places a bot from the map at where the local player is pointing.

bot_quota.doc: Determines the total number of bots in the game.

bot_quota_mode.doc: Determines the type of quota. Allowed values: 'normal', 'fill', and 'match'. If 'fill', the server will adjust bots to keep N players in the game, where N is bot_quota. If 'match', the server will maintain a 1:N ratio of humans to bots, where N is bot_quota.

bot_randombuy.doc: should bots ignore their prefered weapons and just buy weapons at random?

bot_show_battlefront.doc: Show areas where rushing players will initially meet.

bot_show_occupy_time.doc: Show when each nav area can first be reached by each team.

bot_snipers_only.doc: Restricts the bots to only using sniper rifles

bot_zombie.doc: If nonzero, bots will stay in idle mode and not attack.

buddha.doc: Player takes damage but won't die

buddha_reset_hp.doc: HP to set when damaged below zero in Buddha Mode

buymenu.doc: Show or hide main buy menu

buyrandom.doc: Buy random primary and secondary. Primarily for deathmatch where cost is not an issue.

callvote.doc: Start a vote on an issue.

cam_collision.doc: When in thirdperson and cam_collision is set to 1, an attempt is made to keep the camera from passing though walls.

cam_idealdelta.doc: Controls the speed when matching offset to ideal angles in thirdperson view

cam_ideallag.doc: Amount of lag used when matching offset to ideal angles in thirdperson view

cam_showangles.doc: When in thirdperson, print viewangles/idealangles/cameraoffsets to the console.

cc_delay_time.doc: Close caption delay before showing caption.

cc_lang.doc: Current close caption language (emtpy = use game UI language)

cc_subtitles.doc: If set, don't show sound effect captions, just voice overs (i.e., won't help hearing impaired players).

cl_buywheel_donate_key.doc: Set the key to use for donation in the buy menu. 0: Left Control; 1: Left Alt; 2: Left Shift.

cl_buywheel_nonumberpurchasing.doc: Set non-zero to prevent buy wheel from purchasing via number keys

cl_clock_correction.doc: Enable/disable clock correction on the client.

cl_clock_correction_adjustment_max_amoun.doc: Sets the maximum number of milliseconds per second it is allowed to correct the client clock. It will only correct this amount if the difference between the client and server clock is equal to or larger than cl_clock_correction_adjustment_max_offset.

cl_clock_correction_adjustment_max_offse.doc: As the clock offset goes from cl_clock_correction_adjustment_min_offset to this value (in milliseconds), it moves towards applying cl_clock_correction_adjustment_max_amount of adjustment. That way, the response is small when the offset is small.

cl_clock_correction_adjustment_min_offse.doc: If the clock offset is less than this amount (in milliseconds), then no clock correction is applied.

cl_clock_correction_force_server_tick.doc: Force clock correction to match the server tick + this offset (-999 disables it).

cl_clockdrift_max_ticks.doc: Maximum number of ticks the clock is allowed to drift before the client snaps its clock to the server's.

cl_clutch_mode.doc: Silence voice and other distracting sounds until the end of round or next death.

cl_connectionretrytime_p2p.doc: Number of seconds over which to spread retry attempts for P2P.

cl_cq_min_queue.doc: Allows client to disable (=-1), defer to server (=0), or request a certain min-command queue size for games that support the command queue (IsUsingCommandQueue()) for CUserCmds.

cl_crosshair_drawoutline.doc: Draws a black outline around the crosshair for better visibility

cl_crosshair_dynamic_maxdist_splitratio.doc: If using cl_crosshairstyle 2, this is the ratio used to determine how long the inner and outer xhair pips will be. [inner = cl_crosshairsize*(1-cl_crosshair_dynamic_maxdist_splitratio), outer = cl_crosshairsize*cl_crosshair_dynamic_maxdist_splitratio]  [0 - 1]

cl_crosshair_dynamic_splitalpha_innermod.doc: If using cl_crosshairstyle 2, this is the alpha modification that will be used for the INNER crosshair pips once they've split. [0 - 1]

cl_crosshair_dynamic_splitalpha_outermod.doc: If using cl_crosshairstyle 2, this is the alpha modification that will be used for the OUTER crosshair pips once they've split. [0.3 - 1]

cl_crosshair_dynamic_splitdist.doc: If using cl_crosshairstyle 2, this is the distance that the crosshair pips will split into 2. (default is 7)

cl_crosshair_outlinethickness.doc: Set how thick you want your crosshair outline to draw (0-3)

cl_crosshair_sniper_show_normal_inaccura.doc: Include standing inaccuracy when determining sniper crosshair blur

cl_crosshair_sniper_width.doc: If >1 sniper scope cross lines gain extra width (1 for single-pixel hairline)

cl_crosshaircolor.doc: Set crosshair color as defined in game_options.consoles.txt

cl_crosshairgap_useweaponvalue.doc: If set to 1, the gap will update dynamically based on which weapon is currently equipped

cl_crosshairstyle.doc: 0 = DEFAULT (DISABLED), 1 = DEFAULT STATIC (DISABLED), 2 = DEFAULT (accurate recoil/spread feedback with a fixed inner part), 3 = ACCURATE DYNAMIC (DISABLED) (accurate recoil/spread feedback), 4 = DEFAULT STATIC, 5 = LEGACY (fake recoil - inaccurate feedback)

cl_deathcam_audio_mix_phase1_fade_amount.doc: Sets the amount of ducking to do on death cam fade out. When set to 1, full DeathFadeLayer is applied.

cl_deathcam_audio_mix_phase1_fade_time.doc: Sets the amount of time we fade out over.

cl_deathcam_audio_mix_phase2_fade_amount.doc: Sets the amount of ducking to do on death cam fade out. When set to 1, full DeathFadeLayer is applied.

cl_deathcam_audio_mix_phase2_fade_time.doc: Sets the amount of time we fade out over.

cl_deathcampanel_position_dynamic.doc: Turn on/off deathcam's kill panel dynamic Y movement

cl_debounce_zoom.doc: Whether or not to disable holding secondary fire to cycle zoom levels

cl_debugoverlay_cycle_state.doc: Toggles visibility of the debug overlay system.

cl_debugoverlay_toggle.doc: Toggles visibility of the debug overlay system.

cl_disable_deathcam_audio_mix_fade_out.doc: When set to true, disables audio being silenced while the death cam fades out.

cl_dm_buyrandomweapons.doc: Player will automatically receive a random weapon on spawn in deathmatch if this is set to 1 (otherwise, they will receive the last weapon)

cl_draw_only_deathnotices.doc: For drawing only the crosshair and death notices (used for moviemaking)

cl_drawcross.doc: Draws a cross at the given location  Arguments: x y z

cl_drawhud.doc: Enable the rendering of the hud

cl_drawhud_force_deathnotices.doc: 0: default; 1: draw deathnotices even if hud disabled; -1: force no deathnotices

cl_drawhud_force_radar.doc: 0: default; 1: draw radar even if hud disabled; -1: force no radar

cl_drawhud_force_teamid_overhead.doc: 0: default; 1: draw teamid even if hud disabled; -1: force no teamid

cl_drawhud_specvote.doc: 1: default; 0: disables vote UI for spectators

cl_ent_actornames.doc: Displays the entity name for all entities that have ShouldDisplayInActorNames true in code

cl_ent_bbox.doc: Displays the movement bounding box for the given entity(ies) in orange.  Some entites will also display entity specific overlays.  Arguments:    {entity_name} / {class_name} / {entity_index} / {no argument = pick what player is looking at}

cl_ent_grab.doc: grabs the object in front of the player. Options: -loose -multiple -toggle

cl_ent_picker.doc: Toggles 'picker' mode.  When picker is on, the bounding box, pivot and debugging text is displayed for whatever entity the player is looking at.  Arguments: full - enables all debug information

cl_ent_pivot.doc: Displays the pivot for the given entity(ies).  (y=up=green, z=forward=blue, x=left=red).   Arguments:    {entity_name} / {class_name} / {entity_index} / {no argument = pick what player is looking at}

cl_ent_show_damage.doc: Sets damage display mode.  When on, you will see the amount of damage dealt over the target's head.

cl_ent_text256.doc: Displays text debugging information about the given entity(ies) [within 256 units of the player] on top of the entity (See Overlay Text)  Arguments:    {entity_name} / {class_name} / {entity_index} / {no argument = pick what player is looking at}

cl_ent_text_clear.doc: Hide text debugging information about the given entity(ies) on top of the entity (See Overlay Text)  Arguments:    {entity_name} / {class_name} / {entity_index} / {no argument = pick what player is looking at}

cl_ent_text_filter.doc: Set which ent_text filters you want:

cl_extrapolate.doc: Enable/disable extrapolation if interpolation history runs out.

cl_extrapolate_amount.doc: Set how many seconds the client will extrapolate entities for.

cl_fixedcrosshairgap.doc: For crosshair style 1: How big to make the gap between the pips in the fixed crosshair

cl_flushentitypacket.doc: For debugging. Force the engine to flush an entity packet.

cl_hide_avatar_images.doc: Hide avatar images for other players.   0 - Off.  1 - Block All  2 - Block all but friends

cl_http_log_enable.doc: Allows sending HTTP log from client main menu.

cl_hud_color.doc: 0 = team color, 1 = white, 2 = bright white, 3 = light blue, 4 = blue, 5 = purple, 6 = red, 7 = orange, 8 = yellow, 9 = green, 10 = aqua, 11 = pink.

cl_ignorepackets.doc: Force client to ignore packets (for debugging).

cl_interp_hermite.doc: Set to zero do disable hermite interpolation.

cl_interpolate_report.doc: Enable to show interpolation profile timing

cl_inventory_radial_immediate_select.doc: In inventory selection radials. Select weapons the moment the cursor highlights them. Otherwise, only select the selected item on exit.

cl_inventory_radial_tap_to_cycle.doc: In inventory selection radials. Select weapons the moment the cursor highlights them. Otherwise, only select the selected item on exit.

cl_invites_only_friends.doc: If turned on, will ignore in-game invites from recent teammates or other non-friends

cl_invites_only_mainmenu.doc: If turned on, will ignore all invites when user is playing a match

cl_itemimages_dynamically_generated.doc: 2: use render-targets, fallback to cache and disk; 1: no render targets, but use cache and fallback to disk; 0: disk assets only

cl_join_advertise.doc: Advertise joinable game in progress to Steam friends, otherwise need a Steam invite (2: all servers, 1: official servers, 0: none)

cl_lagcompensation.doc: Perform server side lag compensation of weapon firing events.

cl_latch_report.doc: Enable to output stats about latching

cl_mouselook.doc: Set to 1 to use mouse for look, 0 for keyboard look. Cannot be set while connected to a server.

cl_mute_all_but_friends_and_party.doc: Only allow communication from friends and matchmaking party members. Set to 1 to apply the in non-competitive game modes. Set to 2 will apply the setting in all modes.

cl_mute_enemy_team.doc: Block all communication from players on the enemy team.

cl_new_user_phase.doc: 0: Not Started, 1: Needs Training, 2: Training Complete, -1: Disabled

cl_observed_bot_crosshair.doc: Control the crosshair shown when observing a bot. 0: Show player crosshair. 1: Show player crosshair only when bot can be taken over, otherwise show default.. 2: Always show default crosshair for bots.

cl_pdump.doc: Dump info about this entity to screen.

cl_phys_debug_callback_entities.doc: Print all entities that get touch callbacks. Each entity is printed only once.

cl_phys_sleep_enable.doc: Enable sleeping for dynamic physics bodies.

cl_ping_fade_deadzone.doc: Distance from the crosshair over which the ping is completely invisible

cl_ping_fade_distance.doc: Distance from the crosshair over which the ping fades

cl_player_ping_mute.doc: If 1, player pinging will make a sound, if 0, pings will be silent

cl_playerspray_auto_apply.doc: Automatically apply graffiti when graffiti menu closes

cl_predictweapons.doc: Perform client side prediction of weapon effects.

cl_prop_debug.doc: Toggle prop debug mode. If on, props will show colorcoded bounding boxes. Red means ignore all damage. White means respond physically to damage but never break. Green maps health in the range of 100 down to 1.

cl_querycache_stats.doc: Display status of the query cache (client only)

cl_radar_always_centered.doc: If set to 0, the radar is maximally used. Otherwise the player is always centered, even at map extents.

cl_radar_icon_scale_min.doc: Sets the minimum icon scale. Valid values are 0.4 to 1.25.

cl_radar_scale.doc: Sets the radar scale. Valid values are 0.25 to 1.0.

cl_radar_square_with_scoreboard.doc: If set, the radar will toggle to square when the scoreboard is visible.

cl_radial_radio_tap_to_ping.doc: When tapping the radial radio button, leave a ping if nothing is selected within the time in seconds set in cl_radial_menu_tap_duration

cl_ragdoll_limit.doc: Maximum number of ragdolls to show (-1 disables limit)

cl_ragdoll_workaround_threshold.doc: Mainly cosmetic, client-only effect: when client doesn't know the last position of another player that spawns a ragdoll, the ragdoll creation is simplified and ragdoll is created in the right place. If you increase this significantly, ragdoll positions on your client may be dramatically wrong, but it won't affect other clients

cl_rebuy.doc: The order in which rebuy will attempt to repurchase items

mp_consecutive_loss_aversion.doc: How loss streak is affected with round win: 0 = win fully resets loss bonus, 1 = first win steps down loss bonus, 2 = first win holds loss bonus and step down starting with second win

mp_coop_force_join_ct.doc: If set, real players will auto join CT on join.

mp_coopmission_bot_difficulty_offset.doc: The difficulty offset modifier for bots during coop missions.

mp_coopmission_mission_number.doc: Which mission the map should run after it loads.

mp_coopterrorhunt_kill_add_time.doc: The number of seconds added to the clock when players get a kill.

mp_coopterrorhunt_num_enemies.doc: The number of enemies CTs have to hunt and kill.

mp_ct_default_grenades.doc: The default grenades that the CTs will spawn with.  To give multiple grenades, separate each weapon class with a space like this: 'weapon_molotov weapon_hegrenade'

mp_ct_default_melee.doc: The default melee weapon that the CTs will spawn with.  Even if this is blank, a knife will be given. To give a taser, it should look like this: 'weapon_knife weapon_taser'.  Remember to set mp_weapons_allow_zeus to 1 if you want to give a taser!

mp_ct_default_primary.doc: The default primary (rifle) weapon that the CTs will spawn with

mp_ct_default_secondary.doc: The default secondary (pistol) weapon that the CTs will spawn with

mp_damage_headshot_only.doc: Determines whether non-headshot hits do any damage.

mp_damage_scale_ct_body.doc: Scales the damage a CT player takes by this much when they take damage in the body. (1 == 100%, 0.5 == 50%)

mp_damage_scale_ct_head.doc: Scales the damage a CT player takes by this much when they take damage in the head (1 == 100%, 0.5 == 50%).  REMEMBER! headshots do 4x the damage of the body before this scaler is applied.

mp_damage_scale_t_body.doc: Scales the damage a T player takes by this much when they take damage in the body. (1 == 100%, 0.5 == 50%)

mp_damage_scale_t_head.doc: Scales the damage a T player takes by this much when they take damage in the head (1 == 100%, 0.5 == 50%).  REMEMBER! headshots do 4x the damage of the body before this scaler is applied.

mp_damage_vampiric_amount.doc: If Set to non-0, will determine the fraction of damage dealt that will be given to attacker.

mp_death_drop_grenade.doc: Which grenade to drop on player death: 0=none, 1=best, 2=current or best, 3=all grenades

mp_death_drop_gun.doc: Which gun to drop on player death: 0=none, 1=best, 2=current or best

mp_deathcam_skippable.doc: Determines whether a player can early-out of the deathcam.

mp_default_team_winner_no_objective.doc: If the map doesn't define an objective (bomb, hostage, etc), the value of this convar will declare the winner when the time runs out in the round.

mp_defuser_allocation.doc: How to allocate defusers to CTs at start or round: 0=none, 1=random, 2=everyone

mp_disable_autokick.doc: Prevents a userid from being auto-kicked

mp_disconnect_kills_bots.doc: When a bot disconnects, kill them first.  Requires mp_disconnect_kills_players.

mp_disconnect_kills_players.doc: When a player disconnects, kill them first (triggering item drops, stats, etc.)

mp_display_kill_assists.doc: Whether to display and score player assists

mp_dm_bonus_length_max.doc: Maximum time the bonus time will last (in seconds)

mp_dm_bonus_length_min.doc: Minimum time the bonus time will last (in seconds)

mp_dm_bonus_percent.doc: Percent of points additionally awarded when someone gets a kill with the bonus weapon during the bonus period.

mp_dm_bonusweapon_dogtags.doc: Additional dogtags to drop when making a kill with the bonus weapon

mp_dm_dogtag_score.doc: Points to award for picking up a dogtag in deathmatch.

mp_dm_healthshot_killcount.doc: Grant healthshots in deathmatch after n kills

mp_dm_kill_base_score.doc: Number of base points to award for a kill in deathmatch.  Cheaper weapons award 1 or 2 additional points.

mp_dm_teammode.doc: In deathmatch, enables team DM visuals & scoring (0: personal, 1: team mode, 2: use team contribution score)

mp_dm_teammode_bonus_score.doc: Team deathmatch victory points to award for kill with bonus weapon

mp_dm_teammode_dogtag_score.doc: Team deathmatch victory points to award for collecting enemy dogtags

mp_dm_teammode_kill_score.doc: Team deathmatch victory points to award for enemy kill

mp_dm_time_between_bonus_max.doc: Maximum time a bonus time will start after the round start or after the last bonus (in seconds)

mp_dm_time_between_bonus_min.doc: Minimum time a bonus time will start after the round start or after the last bonus (in seconds)

mp_dogtag_despawn_on_killer_death.doc: Whether dogtags should despawn when their killer dies

mp_dogtag_despawn_time.doc: How many seconds dogtags should stay around before despawning automatically (0 = infinite)

mp_dogtag_pickup_rule.doc: Who is eligible to pick up a dogtag (0 = killer only, 1 = killer's team, 2 = victim's team, 3 = killer & victim's team, 4 = anyone)

mp_economy_reset_rounds.doc: Reset all player money every N rounds (0 for never)

mp_endmatch_votenextleveltime.doc: If mp_endmatch_votenextmap is set, players have this much time to vote on the next map at match end.

mp_endmatch_votenextmap.doc: Whether or not players vote for the next map at the end of the match when the final scoreboard comes up

mp_endmatch_votenextmap_keepcurrent.doc: If set, keeps the current map in the list of voting options.  If not set, the current map will not appear in the list of voting options.

mp_endmatch_votenextmap_wargames_modes.doc: Modes available for endmatch voting during War Games. Separate names with spaces.

mp_endmatch_votenextmap_wargames_nummaps.doc: Maximum number of maps to include in endmatch voting during War Games

mp_endmatch_votenextmap_wargames_nummode.doc: Maximum number of other War Games to include in endmatch voting during War Games

mp_endwarmup_player_count.doc: Number of players required to be connected to end warmup early. 0 to require maximum players for mode.

mp_equipment_reset_rounds.doc: Reset all player equipment every N rounds (0 for never)

mp_fists_replace_melee.doc: If enabled then when melee weapon is dropped player will have fists, when melee weapon is picked up then fists are unavailable

mp_footsteps_serverside.doc: Makes the server always play footstep sounds. Clients never calculate footstep sounds locally, instead relying on the server.

mp_force_pick_time.doc: The amount of time a player has on the team screen to make a selection before being auto-teamed

mp_forcecamera.doc: Restricts spectator modes for dead players

mp_free_armor.doc: Determines whether kevlar (1+) and/or helmet (2+) are given automatically.

mp_freezetime.doc: how many seconds to keep players frozen when the round starts

mp_friendlyfire.doc: Allows team members to injure other members of their team

mp_give_player_c4.doc: Whether this map should spawn a c4 bomb for a player or not.

mp_global_damage_per_second.doc: If above 0, deal non-lethal damage to players over time.

mp_guardian_ai_bt_difficulty_adjust_wave.doc: Adjust the guardian bots' difficulty every nth guardian wave when using behavior trees.

mp_guardian_ai_bt_difficulty_cap_beginni.doc: Starting this round a difficulty cap will be applied to the bots.

mp_guardian_ai_bt_difficulty_initial_val.doc: Starting difficulty level for the gardian bots.

mp_guardian_ai_bt_difficulty_max_next_le.doc: How many bots to increase difficulty per wave - this many easier bots will get harder.

mp_guardian_bomb_plant_custom_x_mark_loc.doc: x,y,z to display an X for the bomb plant in guardian missions with custom bomb plant boundaries.

mp_guardian_bot_money_per_wave.doc: The amount of money bots get time each wave the players complete.  This # is absolute and not additive, the money is set to (this)x(wave#) for each bot on each wave.

mp_guardian_force_collect_hostages_timeo.doc: Force bots to collect hostages after this amount of time if no enemy has been seen.

mp_guardian_give_random_grenades_to_bots.doc: If set guardian bots will be given grenades at the beginning of the wave.

mp_guardian_loc_string_hud.doc: Loc string token to use on hud for this mission, otherwise default to kills with weapon.

mp_guardian_loc_weapon.doc: Override to weapon dialog var applied to UI

mp_guardian_player_dist_max.doc: The maximum distance a player is allowed to get from the bombsite before they're killed.

mp_guardian_player_dist_min.doc: The distance at which we start to warn a player when they are too far from the guarded bombsite.

mp_guardian_special_kills_needed.doc: The number of kills needed with a specific weapon.

mp_guardian_special_weapon_needed.doc: The weapon that needs to be used to increment the kills needed to complete the mission.

mp_guardian_target_site.doc: If set to the index of a bombsite, will cause random spawns to be only created near that site.

mp_halftime.doc: Determines whether the match switches sides in a halftime event.

mp_halftime_duration.doc: Target number of seconds that halftime lasts; shortened if team intros are active

mp_halftime_pausematch.doc: Set to 1 to pause match after halftime countdown elapses. Match must be resumed by vote or admin.

mp_halftime_pausetimer.doc: Set to 1 to stay in halftime indefinitely. Set to 0 to resume the timer.

mp_heavyassaultsuit_aimpunch.doc: How much EXTRA aim punch will happen when a player wearing the assault suit gets when shot

mp_heavyassaultsuit_deploy_timescale.doc: How fast a player wearing the heavy assault suit will draw their weapon (1.0 = normal speed, 0.5 = half speed)

mp_heavyassaultsuit_speed.doc: The max speed of a player when they are wearing the heavy assault suit

mp_heavybot_damage_reduction_scale.doc: How much damage should scale when the player wearing the heavy assault suit is shot (1.0 = no change, 0.5 = half damage)

mp_hostages_max.doc: Maximum number of hostages to spawn.

mp_hostages_rescuetime.doc: Additional time added to round time if a hostage is reached by a CT.

mp_hostages_run_speed_modifier.doc: Default is 1.0, slow down hostages by setting this to < 1.0.

mp_hostages_spawn_farthest.doc: When enabled will consistently force the farthest hostages to spawn.

mp_hostages_spawn_force_positions.doc: Comma separated list of zero based indices to force spawn positions, e.g. '0,2' or '1,6'

mp_hostages_spawn_force_positions_xyz.doc: Comma separated list of xyz locations to force spawn positions, e.g. 'x1 y1 z1,x2 y2 z2'

mp_hostages_spawn_same_every_round.doc: 0 = spawn hostages randomly every round, 1 = same spawns for entire match.

mp_hostages_takedamage.doc: Whether or not hostages can be hurt.

mp_humanteam.doc: Restricts human players to a single team {any, CT, T}

mp_ignore_round_win_conditions.doc: Ignore conditions which would end the current round

mp_items_prohibited.doc: Set this convar to a comma-delimited list of definition indices of weapons that should be prohibited from use.

mp_join_grace_time.doc: Number of seconds after round start to allow a player to join a game

mp_limitteams.doc: Max # of players 1 team can have over another (0 disables check)

mp_logdetail_items.doc: Logs a line any time a player acquires or loses an item.

mp_logdistance_2d.doc: Enables distance logging every so many units

mp_logdistance_sec.doc: Enables distance logging every so many seconds

mp_logloadouts.doc: Enables distance logging with full loadouts

mp_match_can_clinch.doc: Can a team clinch and end the match by being so far ahead that the other team has no way to catching up?

mp_match_end_changelevel.doc: At the end of the match, perform a changelevel even if next map is the same

mp_match_end_restart.doc: At the end of the match, perform a restart instead of loading a new map

mp_match_restart_delay.doc: Time (in seconds) until a match restarts.

mp_max_armor.doc: Determines the highest level of armor allowed to be purchased. (0) None, (1) Kevlar, (2) Helmet

mp_maxmoney.doc: maximum amount of money allowed in a player's account

mp_maxrounds.doc: max number of rounds to play before server changes maps

mp_min_halftime_duration.doc: Minimum number of seconds that halftime lasts even if team intros are active

mp_overtime_enable.doc: If a match ends in a tie, use overtime rules to determine winner

mp_overtime_halftime_pausetimer.doc: If set to 1 will set mp_halftime_pausetimer to 1 before every half of overtime. Set mp_halftime_pausetimer to 0 to resume the timer.

mp_overtime_limit.doc: When overtime is enabled, only so many overtimes can be played

mp_overtime_maxrounds.doc: When overtime is enabled play additional rounds to determine winner

mp_overtime_startmoney.doc: Money assigned to all players at start of every overtime half

mp_pause_match.doc: Pause the match in the next freeze time

mp_playercashawards.doc: Players can earn money by performing in-game actions

mp_playerid.doc: Controls what information player see in the status bar: 0 all names; 1 team names; 2 no names

mp_playerid_delay.doc: Number of seconds to delay showing information in the status bar

mp_playerid_hold.doc: Number of seconds to keep showing old information in the status bar

mp_randomspawn.doc: Determines whether players are to spawn. 0 = default; 1 = both teams; 2 = Terrorists; 3 = CTs.

mp_randomspawn_dist.doc: If using mp_randomspawn, determines whether to test distance when selecting this spot.

mp_randomspawn_los.doc: If using mp_randomspawn, determines whether to test Line of Sight when spawning.

mp_require_gun_use_to_acquire.doc: Whether guns must be +used to acquire or default is touch-to-pickup

mp_respawn_immunitytime.doc: How many seconds after respawn immunity lasts. Set to negative value to disable warmup immunity.

mp_respawn_on_death_ct.doc: When set to 1, counter-terrorists will respawn after dying.

mp_respawn_on_death_t.doc: When set to 1, terrorists will respawn after dying.

mp_respawnwavetime_ct.doc: Time between respawn waves for CTs.

mp_respawnwavetime_t.doc: Time between respawn waves for Terrorists.

mp_restartgame.doc: If non-zero, game will restart in the specified number of seconds

mp_retake_ct_count.doc: Number of CT's when playing retakes.

mp_retake_ct_loadout_bonus_card.doc: CT bonus card for full buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_ct_loadout_bonus_card_availabi.doc: CT bonus card availability pattern for full buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_ct_loadout_default_pistol_roun.doc: CT Loadouts for default pistol round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_ct_loadout_enemy_card.doc: CT enemy card for full buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_ct_loadout_full_buy_round.doc: CT Loadouts for full buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_ct_loadout_light_buy_round.doc: CT Loadouts for force buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_ct_loadout_upgraded_pistol_rou.doc: CT Loadouts for upgraded pistol round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_max_consecutive_rounds_same_ta.doc: Limit the number of consecutive rounds targeting the same site.

mp_retake_t_count.doc: Number of terrorists when playing retakes.

mp_retake_t_loadout_bonus_card.doc: T bonus card for full buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_t_loadout_bonus_card_availabil.doc: T bonus card availability pattern for full buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_t_loadout_default_pistol_round.doc: T Loadouts for default pistol round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_t_loadout_enemy_card.doc: T enemy card for full buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_t_loadout_full_buy_round.doc: T Loadouts for full buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_t_loadout_light_buy_round.doc: T Loadouts for force buy round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_retake_t_loadout_upgraded_pistol_roun.doc: T Loadouts for upgraded pistol round when playing bomb site retake.

mp_round_restart_delay.doc: Number of seconds to delay before restarting a round after a win

mp_roundtime.doc: How many minutes each round takes.

mp_roundtime_defuse.doc: How many minutes each round of Bomb Defuse takes. If 0 then use mp_roundtime instead.

mp_roundtime_deployment.doc: How many minutes deployment for coop mission takes.

mp_roundtime_hostage.doc: How many minutes each round of Hostage Rescue takes. If 0 then use mp_roundtime instead.

mp_scrambleteams.doc: Scramble the teams and restart the game

mp_shield_speed_deployed.doc: The max speed of a player when they have a shield deployed

mp_shield_speed_holstered.doc: The max speed of a player when they have a shield holstered

mp_shorthanded_cash_bonus_ignore_kicked.doc: Determines whether kicked players are included in the assessment for short-handedness

mp_shorthanded_cash_bonus_round_delay.doc: number of previous rounds that a team needs to have been shorthanded before they are eligible for the short-handed bonus

mp_solid_teammates.doc: How solid are teammates: 0 = transparent; 1 = fully solid; 2 = can stand on top of heads

mp_spawnprotectiontime.doc: Kick players who team-kill within this many seconds of a round restart.

mp_spec_swapplayersides.doc: Toggle set the player names and team names to the opposite side in which they are are on the spectator panel.

mp_spectators_max.doc: How many spectators are allowed in a match.

mp_starting_losses.doc: Determines what the initial loss streak is.

mp_startmoney.doc: amount of money each player gets when they reset

mp_swapteams.doc: Swap the teams and restart the game

mp_t_default_grenades.doc: The default grenades that the Ts will spawn with. To give multiple grenades, separate each weapon class with a space like this: 'weapon_molotov weapon_hegrenade'

mp_t_default_melee.doc: The default melee weapon that the Ts will spawn with

mp_t_default_primary.doc: The default primary (rifle) weapon that the Ts will spawn with

mp_t_default_secondary.doc: The default secondary (pistol) weapon that the Ts will spawn with

mp_tagging_scale.doc: Scalar for player tagging modifier when hit. Lower values for greater tagging.

mp_taser_recharge_time.doc: Determines recharge time for taser. -1 = disabled.

mp_td_dmgtokick.doc: The damage threshhold players have to exceed in a match to get kicked.

mp_td_dmgtowarn.doc: The damage threshhold players have to exceed in a match to get warned that they are about to be kicked.

mp_td_spawndmgthreshold.doc: The damage threshold players have to exceed at the start of the round to be warned/kick.

mp_team_intro_time.doc: How many seconds for team intro

mp_team_timeout_max.doc: Number of timeouts each team gets per match.

mp_team_timeout_ot_add_each.doc: Number of timeouts to add for each team when match goes to 2nd and each next overtime.

mp_team_timeout_ot_add_once.doc: Number of timeouts to add for each team when regulation time ends and match goes to overtime.

mp_team_timeout_ot_max.doc: Max number of timeouts each team can have per OT after all OT timeouts got added.

mp_teamcashawards.doc: Teams can earn money by performing in-game actions

mp_teamflag_1.doc: Enter a country's alpha 2 code to show that flag next to team 1's name in the spectator scoreboard.

mp_teamflag_2.doc: Enter a country's alpha 2 code to show that flag next to team 2's name in the spectator scoreboard.

mp_teamlogo_1.doc: Enter a team's shorthand image name to display their logo. Images can be found here: 'resource/flash/econ/tournaments/teams'

mp_teamlogo_2.doc: Enter a team's shorthand image name to display their logo. Images can be found here: 'resource/flash/econ/tournaments/teams'

mp_teammatchstat_1.doc: A non-empty string sets first team's match stat.

mp_teammatchstat_2.doc: A non-empty string sets second team's match stat.

mp_teammatchstat_cycletime.doc: Cycle match stats after so many seconds

mp_teammatchstat_holdtime.doc: Decide on a match stat and hold it additionally for at least so many seconds

mp_teammatchstat_txt.doc: A non-empty string sets the match stat description, e.g. 'Match 2 of 3'.

mp_teammates_are_enemies.doc: When set, your teammates act as enemies and all players are valid targets.

mp_teamname_1.doc: A non-empty string overrides the first team's name.

mp_teamname_2.doc: A non-empty string overrides the second team's name.

mp_teamprediction_pct.doc: A value between 1 and 99 will show predictions in favor of CT team.

mp_teamprediction_txt.doc: A value between 1 and 99 will set predictions in favor of first team.

mp_teamscore_1.doc: A non-empty string for best-of-N maps won by the first team.

mp_teamscore_2.doc: A non-empty string for best-of-N maps won by the second team.

mp_teamscore_max.doc: How many maps to win the series (bo3 max=2; bo5 max=3; bo7 max=4)

mp_technical_timeout_duration_s.doc: How many seconds is a full technical timeout?

mp_technical_timeout_per_team.doc: How many technical timeouts are there per team?

mp_timelimit.doc: game time per map in minutes

mp_tkpunish.doc: Will TK'ers and team damagers be punished in the next round?  {0=no,  1=yes}

mp_use_respawn_waves.doc: When set to 1, and that player's team is set to respawn, they will respawn in waves. If set to 2, teams will respawn when the whole team is dead.

mp_warmup_offline_enabled.doc: Whether or not to do a warmup period at the start of a match in an offline (bot) match.

mp_warmup_online_enabled.doc: Whether or not to do a warmup period at the start of an online match.

mp_warmup_pausetimer.doc: Set to 1 to stay in warmup indefinitely. Set to 0 to resume the timer.

mp_warmuptime.doc: How long the warmup period lasts. Changing this value resets warmup.

mp_warmuptime_all_players_connected.doc: Warmup time to use when all players have connected. 0 to disable.

mp_warmuptime_match_cancelled.doc: Warmup time to use when the match will be cancelled (eg. due to a live VAC ban).

mp_weapon_self_inflict_amount.doc: If Set to non-0, will hurt the attacker by the specified fraction of max damage if they miss.

mp_weapons_allow_heavy.doc: Determines which team, if any, can purchase Heavy guns. -1 = any; 0 = non; 2 = Ts; 3 = CTs.

mp_weapons_allow_map_placed.doc: If this convar is set, when a match starts, the game will not delete weapons placed in the map.

mp_weapons_allow_pistols.doc: Determines which team, if any, can purchase Pistols. -1 = any; 0 = non; 2 = Ts; 3 = CTs.

mp_weapons_allow_rifles.doc: Determines which team, if any, can purchase Rifles. -1 = any; 0 = non; 2 = Ts; 3 = CTs.

mp_weapons_allow_smgs.doc: Determines which team, if any, can purchase SMGs. -1 = any; 0 = non; 2 = Ts; 3 = CTs.

mp_weapons_allow_typecount.doc: Determines how many purchases of each weapon type allowed per player per round (0 to disallow purchasing, -1 to have no limit).

mp_weapons_allow_zeus.doc: Determines how many Zeus purchases a player can make per round (0 to disallow, -1 to have no limit).

mp_weapons_glow_on_ground.doc: If this convar is set, weapons on the ground will have a glow around them.

mp_weapons_max_gun_purchases_per_weapon_.doc: Max number of times a player may purchase any weapon per match

mp_win_panel_display_time.doc: The amount of time to show the win panel between matches / halfs

av_add_to_selected_set.doc: Add current area to the selected set.

av_add_to_selected_set_by_id.doc: Add specified area id to the selected set.

av_avoid.doc: Toggles the 'avoid this area when possible' flag used by the AI system.

av_begin_deselecting.doc: Start continuously removing from the selected set.

av_begin_selecting.doc: Start continuously adding to the selected set.

av_check_connectivity.doc: Checks to be sure every (or just the marked) nav area can get to every goal area for the map (hostages or bomb site).

av_clear_attribute.doc: Remove given nav attribute from all areas in the selected set.

av_clear_attributes.doc: Clear all nav attributes of selected area.

av_corner_adjust_adjacent.doc: radius used to raise/lower corners in nearby areas when raising/lowering corners.

av_delete_all_hull.doc: Deletes all areas with given hull category.

av_delete_marked.doc: Deletes the currently marked Area (if any).

av_disconnect.doc: To disconnect two Areas, mark an Area, highlight a second Area, then invoke the disconnect command. This will remove all connections between the two Areas.

av_draw_attribute_dynamic.doc: Draw all nav areas with this dynamic attribute

av_draw_attribute_game.doc: Draw all nav areas with this game attribute

av_draw_limit.doc: The maximum number of areas to draw in edit mode

av_draw_mesh_grid.doc: Draw the mesh's spatial grid structure around the edit cursor position.

av_draw_mesh_offset.doc: Vertical offset for drawing the mesh (useful for flat planes where the mesh is often a fixed offset from the physical ground

av_edit.doc: Set to one to interactively edit the Navigation Mesh. Set to zero to leave edit mode.

av_end_deselecting.doc: Stop continuously removing from the selected set.

av_end_selecting.doc: Stop continuously adding to the selected set.

av_gen_agent_radius_buffer.doc: Buffer to add to agent radius before passing to nav gen

av_gen_jump_connection_min_overlap_ratio.doc: Minimum edge overlap required for jump connection consideration as a percentage of agent radius

av_lower_drag_volume_max.doc: Lower the top of the drag select volume.

av_lower_drag_volume_min.doc: Lower the bottom of the drag select volume.

av_mark.doc: Marks the Area or Ladder under the cursor for manipulation by subsequent editing commands.

av_mark_attribute.doc: Set nav attribute for all areas in the selected set.

av_max_view_distance.doc: Maximum range for precomputed nav mesh visibility (0 = default 1500 units)

av_precise.doc: Toggles the 'dont avoid obstacles' flag used by the AI system.

av_raise_drag_volume_max.doc: Raise the top of the drag select volume.

av_raise_drag_volume_min.doc: Raise the bottom of the drag select volume.

av_remove_from_selected_set.doc: Remove current area from the selected set.

av_select_allow_blocked.doc: When selecting an area under nav_edit, allow area marked as blocked.

av_select_area_id.doc: Select nav area with matching ID.

av_select_block_id.doc: Select nav space block with matching ID.

av_select_hull.doc: Restrict area selection to areas that can support a hull of the given category

av_select_radius.doc: Adds all areas in a radius to the selection set

av_select_with_attribute.doc: Selects areas with the given attribute.

av_show_area_connections.doc: Show connections to selected area when true

av_show_potentially_visible.doc: Show areas that are potentially visible from the current nav area

av_split.doc: To split an Area into two, align the split line using your cursor and invoke the split command.

av_split_place_on_ground.doc: If true, nav areas will be placed flush with the ground when split.

av_store_selected_set.doc: Stores the current selected set for later retrieval.

av_test_bfs_lattice_hex.doc: Demonstrates searching hexagonal lattice over nav mesh.

av_test_find_nearest.doc: Calculate the nearest point on the navmesh to the trace point.  Uses selection from nav_select_hull.

sv_gameinstructor_enable.doc: Force all clients to enable their game instructors.

sv_grenade_trajectory_prac_pipreview.doc: Shows grenade trajectory practice picture-in-picture preview.

sv_grenade_trajectory_prac_trailtime.doc: Shows grenade trajectory practice visualization for this number of seconds.

sv_grenade_trajectory_time_spectator.doc: Length of time grenade trajectory remains visible as a spectator.

sv_guardian_extra_equipment_ct.doc: Extra starting equipment for CT players in guardian modes

sv_guardian_extra_equipment_t.doc: Extra starting equipment for Terrorist players in guardian modes

sv_guardian_health_refresh_per_wave.doc: Health given to survivors per wave in guardian mode.

sv_guardian_refresh_ammo_for_items_on_wa.doc: List of additional weapons to refill ammo on waves.

sv_guardian_respawn_health.doc: Starting health of guardian players when respawned.

sv_guardian_starting_equipment_humans.doc: Extra starting equipment for human players in guardian modes

sv_hibernate_postgame_delay.doc: # of seconds to wait after final client leaves before hibernating.

sv_hibernate_when_empty.doc: Puts the server into extremely low CPU usage mode when no clients connected

sv_hoststate_quit_syscall.doc: When enabled, game server will quit immediately via syscall instead of running host states shutdown sequence

sv_human_autojoin_team.doc: Force human players on to a team. 0 to disable.

sv_ignoregrenaderadio.doc: Turn off Fire in the hole messages

sv_infinite_ammo.doc: Player's active weapon will never run out of ammo

sv_invites_only_mainmenu.doc: If turned on, will ignore all invites when user is playing a match

sv_jump_impulse.doc: Initial upward velocity for player jumps; sqrt(2*gravity*height).

sv_jump_spam_penalty_time.doc: For subtick jumps, if this much time has elapsed since the last time the user has pressed the jump key, pretend they hadn't. Lowering this makes bunnyhopping easier.

sv_kick_ban_duration.doc: How long should a kick ban from the server should last (in minutes)

sv_kick_players_with_cooldown.doc: (0: do not kick on insecure servers; 1: kick players with Untrusted status or convicted by Overwatch; 2: kick players with any cooldown)

sv_ladder_slack_z_mult.doc: Difference in Z increases toward the middle of the slack ladder.

sv_lagcompensationforcerestore.doc: Don't test validity of a lag comp restore, just do it.

sv_lan.doc: Server is a lan server ( no heartbeat, no authentication, no non-class C addresses )

sv_load_forced_client_names_file.doc: Loads a file containing SteamID64 names for clients

sv_load_random_client_names_file.doc: Loads a file containing random name words for clients

sv_log_onefile.doc: Log server information to only one file.

sv_logbans.doc: Log server bans in the server logs.

sv_logblocks.doc: If true when log when a query is blocked (can cause very large log files)

sv_logecho.doc: Echo log information to the console.

sv_logfile.doc: Log server information in the log file.

sv_logflush.doc: Flush the log file to disk on each write (slow).

sv_logsdir.doc: Folder in the game directory where server logs will be stored.

sv_mapvetopickvote_maps.doc: Which maps are used for map veto pick sequence

sv_mapvetopickvote_phase_duration.doc: 15][3:20][4:10][5:10][6:5] : sv, release                      : How many seconds each phase lasts

sv_mapvetopickvote_rnd.doc: When enabled will shuffle veto pick maps list order every time

sv_matchend_drops_enabled.doc: Rewards gameplay time is always accumulated for players, but drops at the end of the match can be prevented

sv_matchpause_auto_5v5.doc: When enabled will automatically pause the match at next freeze time if less than 5 players are connected on each team.

sv_max_allowed_net_graph.doc: Determines max allowed net_graph value for clients.

sv_max_queries_sec.doc: Maximum queries per second to respond to from a single IP address.

sv_max_queries_sec_global.doc: Maximum queries per second to respond to from anywhere.

sv_max_queries_window.doc: Window over which to average queries per second averages.

sv_maxrate.doc: Max bandwidth rate allowed on server, 0 == unlimited

sv_maxvelocity.doc: Maximum speed any ballistically moving object is allowed to attain per axis.

sv_memlimit.doc: If set, whenever a game ends, if the total memory used by the server is greater than this # of megabytes, the server will exit.

sv_merge_changes_after_tick_with_calcdel.doc: This fixes bugs where pure calcdelta is used due to recipient changing but it doesn't pick up a field change where the value was changed back to same value as the from snapshot even though the destination fields change list does note the change. Set to 2 to spew any changes merged in by this fix.

sv_metaduplication.doc: Check serializer meta for duplication, add verbose to command for full spew

sv_minrate.doc: Min bandwidth rate allowed on server, 0 == unlimited

sv_networkvar_perfieldtracking.doc: Track individual field offset changes, rather than a single dirty flag for the whole entity.

sv_networkvar_validate.doc: Validate each StateChanged against known offsets.

sv_noclipduringpause.doc: If cheats are enabled, then you can noclip with the game paused (for doing screenshots, etc.).

sv_packstats.doc: Show entity packing stats, pass 'clear' as argument to reset counts.

sv_parallel_packentities.doc: Set to 1 to use threaded snapshot sending on listen servers, 2 for dedicated servers.

sv_parallel_sendsnapshot.doc: 0: run all send jobs on main thread; 1: send jobs run asynchronously (except on dedicated server); 2: send jobs asynchronously; 3: send jobs run in parallel but block to not overlap the next tick; 4: main server clients' send jobs run in parallel, then HLTV server jobs; this approximately matches pre-async profile for a single HLTV server configuration

sv_password.doc: Server password for entry into multiplayer games

sv_pause_on_console_open.doc: 1 = Pause the game when pressing ~ to open the console. CTRL+~ opens the console without pause.

sv_phys_debug_callback_entities.doc: Print all entities that get touch callbacks. Each entity is printed only once.

sv_phys_sleep_enable.doc: Enable sleeping for dynamic physics bodies.

sv_playerradio_use_allowlist.doc: playerradio commands may only use responses from an allow list of commands.

sv_prime_accounts_only.doc: When this setting is enabled only prime users can connect to this game server.

sv_pure_kick_clients.doc: If set to 1, the server will kick clients with mismatching files. Otherwise, it will issue a warning to the client.

sv_pure_trace.doc: If set to 1, the server will print a message whenever a client is verifying a CRC for a file.

sv_pushaway_hostage_force.doc: How hard the hostage is pushed away from physics objects (falls off with inverse square of distance).

sv_pushaway_max_hostage_force.doc: Maximum of how hard the hostage is pushed away from physics objects.

sv_pvs_max_distance.doc: if set, adds a maximum range to PVS/PAS checks

sv_radio_throttle_window.doc: The number of seconds before radio command tokens refresh.

sv_record_item_time_data.doc: Turn on recording of per player item time data into the server log.

sv_regeneration_force_on.doc: Cheat to test regenerative health systems

sv_region.doc: The region of the world to report this server in.

sv_rethrow_last_grenade.doc: Emit the last grenade thrown on the server.

sv_search_team_key.doc: When initiating team search, set this key to match with known opponents team

sv_server_graphic1.doc: A 360x60 (<16kb) image file in /csgo/ that will be displayed to spectators.

sv_server_graphic2.doc: A 220x45 (<16kb) image file in /csgo/ that will be displayed to spectators.

sv_show_move_collisions.doc: Enable this to visualize collisions between player and geometry.

sv_show_teammate_death_notification.doc: Show chat notification upon teammate death

sv_show_voip_indicator_for_enemies.doc: Makes it so the voip icon is shown over enemies as well as allies when they are talking

sv_showbullethits.doc: 1=show hits and near misses, 2=show hits only

sv_showhitregistration.doc: Display lag_compensated hitboxes. 0 = off, 1 = server only, 2 = client only, 3 = both server and client

sv_showimpacts.doc: Shows client (red) and server (blue) bullet impact point (1=both, 2=client-only, 3=server-only)

sv_showimpacts_penetration.doc: Shows extra data when bullets penetrate. (use sv_showimpacts_time to increase time shown)

sv_showimpacts_time.doc: Duration bullet impact indicators remain before disappearing

sv_shutdown.doc: Sets the server to shutdown when all games have completed

sv_skirmish_id.doc: Dedicated server skirmish id to run

sv_skyname.doc: Current name of the skybox texture

sv_snapshot_unlimited.doc: For debugging, don't throw away old snapshots so that if you break in debugger (on remote client or server) it won't require an uncompressed update to resume.  You may run out of memory of course...

sv_spawn_afk_bomb_drop_time.doc: Players that have never moved since they spawned will drop the bomb after this amount of time.

sv_spec_hear.doc: Determines who spectators can hear: 0: only spectators; 1: all players; 2: spectated team; 3: self only; 4: nobody

sv_steamgroup.doc: The ID of the steam group that this server belongs to. You can find your group's ID on the admin profile page in the steam community.

sv_steamgroup_exclusive.doc: If set, only members of Steam group will be able to join the server when it's empty, public people will be able to join the server only if it has players.

sv_stopspeed.doc: Minimum stopping speed when on ground.

sv_stressbots.doc: If set to 1, the server calculates data and fills packets to bots. Used for perf testing.

sv_tags.doc: Server tags. Used to provide extra information to clients when they're browsing for servers. Separate tags with a comma.

sv_talk_after_dying_time.doc: The number of seconds a player can continue talking after dying as if they were still alive

sv_talk_enemy_dead.doc: Dead players can hear all dead enemy communication (voice, chat)

sv_talk_enemy_living.doc: Living players can hear all living enemy communication (voice, chat)

sv_teamid_overhead.doc: Shows teamID over player's heads.  0 = off, 1 = on

sv_timebetweenducks.doc: Minimum time before recognizing consecutive duck key

sv_update_animgraph_movement_in_finish.doc: Whether we should update animgraph movement in FinishMove.

sv_usercmd_custom_random_seed.doc: When enabled server will populate an additional random seed independent of the client

sv_usercmd_queue_spew_threshold.doc: Spew warning if command queue has grown above this many backlogged commands.

sv_versus_screen_scene_id.doc: Determines which scene is used for the versus screen.

sv_visiblemaxplayers.doc: Overrides the max players reported to prospective clients

sv_voicecodec.doc: Specifies which voice codec DLL to use in a game. Set to the name of the DLL without the extension.

sv_vote_command_delay.doc: How long after a vote passes until the action happens

sv_vote_count_spectator_votes.doc: Allow spectators to vote on issues?

sv_vote_creation_timer.doc: How often someone can individually call a vote.

sv_vote_disallow_kick_on_match_point.doc: Disallow vote kicking on the match point round.

sv_vote_failure_timer.doc: A vote that fails cannot be re-submitted for this long

sv_vote_issue_kick_allowed.doc: Can people hold votes to kick players from the server?

sv_vote_issue_loadbackup_allowed.doc: Can people hold votes to load match from backup?

sv_vote_issue_loadbackup_spec_authoritat.doc: When enabled, admins load match from backup without players vote

sv_vote_issue_loadbackup_spec_only.doc: When enabled, only admins load match from backup

sv_vote_issue_loadbackup_spec_safe.doc: When enabled, admins load match from backup in safe time of the round only

sv_vote_issue_pause_match_spec_only.doc: When enabled, only admins start technical pause

sv_vote_issue_restart_game_allowed.doc: Can people hold votes to restart the game?

sv_vote_kick_ban_duration.doc: How long should a kick vote ban someone from the server? (in minutes)

sv_vote_quorum_ratio.doc: The minimum ratio of players needed to vote on an issue to resolve it.

sv_vote_timer_duration.doc: How long to allow voting on an issue

sv_vote_to_changelevel_before_match_poin.doc: Restricts vote to change level to rounds prior to match point (default 0, vote is never disallowed)

sv_warmup_to_freezetime_delay.doc: Delay between end of warmup and start of match.

sv_watchtransmit.doc: Watch NetworkStateChanged info for this entity index.

sv_weapon_swap_difficulty_near_hi_pri.doc: 0 = Cone searches easily reach past high priority items to swap weapons. 1 = Cone searches are narrowed and require that the weapon is strictly closer. 2 = cone searches are disabled near high priority items

sv_workshop_allow_other_maps.doc: When hosting a workshop collection, users can play other workshop map on this server when it is empty and then mapcycle into this server collection.

sys_info.doc: Print system information to the console

sys_minidumpspewlines.doc: Lines of crash dump console spew to keep.

telemetry_message.doc: Place a message in the telemetry timeline

telemetry_toggle_timespan.doc: Starts/stops a timespan with an ever increasing name.

test_dispatcheffect.doc: Test a clientside dispatch effect.  Usage: test_dispatcheffect <effect name> <distance away> <flags> <magnitude> <scale>  Defaults are: <distance 1024> <flags 0> <magnitude 0> <scale 0>

test_entity_blocker.doc: Test command that drops an entity blocker out in front of the player.

Test_ExitProcess.doc: Test_ExitProcess <exit code> - immediately kill the process.

think_limit.doc: Maximum think time in milliseconds, warning is printed if this is exceeded.

thirdperson_mayamode.doc: Switch to thirdperson Maya-like camera controls.

timedemo.doc: Play a demo and report performance info.

timedemoquit.doc: Play a demo, report performance info, and then exit

timeleft.doc: prints the time remaining in the match

toggle.doc: Toggles specified convar value on and off.

tv_advertise_watchable.doc: GOTV advertises the match as watchable via game UI, clients watching via UI will not need to type password

tv_allow_autorecording_index.doc: When >=0 restricts autorecording only to the specified TV index

tv_allow_camera_man_steamid.doc: Allows tournament production cameraman to run csgo.exe -interactivecaster on SteamID 7650123456XXX and be the camera man.

tv_allow_camera_man_steamid2.doc: Allows tournament production tv cameraman to run csgo.exe -interactivecaster on SteamID 7650123456XXX and be the tv camera man.

tv_allow_static_shots.doc: Auto director uses fixed level cameras for shots

tv_autorecord.doc: Automatically records all games as SourceTV demos.

tv_autoretry.doc: Relay proxies retry connection after network timeout

tv_broadcast.doc: Automatically broadcasts all games as GOTV demos through Steam.

tv_broadcast1.doc: Automatically broadcasts all games as GOTV[1] demos through Steam.

tv_broadcast_keyframe_interval.doc: The frequency, in seconds, of sending keyframes and delta fragments to the broadcast relay server

tv_broadcast_keyframe_interval1.doc: The frequency, in seconds, of sending keyframes and delta fragments to the broadcast1 relay server

tv_broadcast_max_requests.doc: Max number of broadcast http requests in flight. If there is a network issue, the requests may start piling up, degrading server performance. If more than the specified number of requests are in flight, the new requests are dropped.

tv_broadcast_max_requests1.doc: Max number of broadcast1 http requests in flight. If there is a network issue, the requests may start piling up, degrading server performance. If more than the specified number of requests are in flight, the new requests are dropped.

tv_broadcast_startup_resend_interval.doc: The interval, in seconds, of re-sending startup data to the broadcast relay server (useful in case relay crashes, restarts or startup data http request fails)

tv_broadcast_url.doc: 8080 : release                          : URL of the broadcast relay

tv_broadcast_url1.doc: 8080 : release                          : URL of the broadcast relay1

tv_chatgroupsize.doc: Set the default chat group size

tv_chattimelimit.doc: Limits spectators to chat only every n seconds

tv_clients.doc: Shows list of connected SourceTV clients.

tv_delaymapchange.doc: Delays map change until broadcast is complete

tv_deltacache.doc: Enable delta entity bit stream cache

tv_dispatchmode.doc: Dispatch clients to relay proxies: 0=never, 1=if appropriate, 2=always

tv_enable_delta_frames.doc: Indicates whether or not the tv should use delta frames for storage of intermediate frames. This takes more CPU but significantly less memory.

tv_enable_dynamic.doc: When enabled, changes in tv_enable convars cause immediate startup or shutdown of hltv server

tv_listen_voice_indices.doc: Bitfield of playerslots to listen to voice messages from when connected to SourceTV, default is none

tv_listen_voice_indices_h.doc: High 32 bits of bitfield of playerslots to listen to voice messages from when connected to SourceTV, default is none

tv_maxclients.doc: Maximum client number on SourceTV server.

tv_maxclients_relayreserved.doc: This number of relay client connections are reserved for SourceTV relays.

tv_maxrate.doc: Max SourceTV spectator bandwidth rate allowed, 0 == unlimited

tv_mem.doc: hltv memory statistics. Use with 'ent 10' (dump entity 10 memory usage) or 'top 8' (dump top 8 memory users) or 'class' CWorld (dump CWorld class)

tv_nochat.doc: Don't receive chat messages from other SourceTV spectators

tv_overridemaster.doc: Overrides the SourceTV master root address.

tv_playcast_delay_resync.doc: To alleviate intermittent network connectivity problems, this is the number of seconds to wait before actually re-syncing the stream after failure

tv_playcast_retry_timeout.doc: In case of intermittent network problems, how long should playcast retry fragment retrieval before resorting to resync

tv_record_immediate.doc: tv_record starting the moment tv_record was executed, not tv_delay earlier

tv_relay.doc: Connect to SourceTV server and relay broadcast.

tv_relayradio.doc: Relay team radio commands to TV: 0=off, 1=on

tv_title.doc: Set title for SourceTV spectator UI

tv_transmitall.doc: Transmit all entities (not only director view)

ui_party_msg_sound_enabled.doc: When enabled, lobby messages will play a short sound

ui_setting_advertiseforhire_auto.doc: Whether users will automatically advertise for invites (0: off; 1: last; 2: auto)

ui_setting_advertiseforhire_auto_last.doc: Which game mode users last used to advertise for invites

ui_steam_overlay_notification_position_h.doc: Steam overlay notification position horizontal offset

ui_steam_overlay_notification_position_v.doc: Steam overlay notification position vertical offset

unpause.doc: Clear the pause state of the server.

vconsole_rcon_server_details.doc: when non-empty allows for easy vconsole connection to the dedicated server.

view_punch_decay.doc: Decay factor exponent for view punch

viewmodel_always_on.doc: Force the view model to draw, even when in 3rd person

viewmodel_offset_randomize.doc: randomly change viewmodel offsets to visualize range

vmix_output.doc: Dump main graph control output values

voice_always_sample_mic.doc: For systems experiencing a hang/stall when using voice chat.

voice_vox.doc: Voice chat uses a vox-style always on

weapon_accuracy_forcespread.doc: Force spread to the specified value.

weapon_accuracy_reset_on_deploy.doc: On deploy, forcibly reset weapon accuracy to zero.

weapon_air_spread_scale.doc: Scale factor for jumping inaccuracy, set to 0 to make jumping accuracy equal to standing

weapon_auto_cleanup_time.doc: If set to non-zero, weapons will delete themselves after the specified time (in seconds) if no players are near.

weapon_debug_spread_show.doc: Enables display of weapon accuracy; 1: show accuracy box, 3: show accuracy with dynamic crosshair

weapon_max_before_cleanup.doc: If set to non-zero, will remove the oldest dropped weapon to maintain the specified number of dropped weapons in the world.

weapon_reticle_knife_show.doc: When enabled will show knife reticle on clients. Used for game modes requiring target id display when holding a knife.

weapon_sound_falloff_multiplier.doc: Scaling for falloff of weapon firing sounds

writekeybindings.doc: Saves current key bindings to disk.

zoom_sensitivity_ratio.doc: Additional mouse sensitivity scale factor applied when FOV is zoomed in.
